article.headline: IUPUI 78, Ball State 60
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Odell Bradley finished with game highs of 23 points and 18 rebounds to lead IUPUI over Ball State 78-60 on Saturday night. Odell finished 8-for-14 from the field and 7-for-11 from the free throw line for the Jaguars (5-3), who led 36-22 at the half and outscored the Cardinals (3-3) by four points in the second half. Ball State was held to 19 percent shooting in the first half (6-32) and improved to 38 percent (14-37) in the second. The Cardinals had just two players in double-figures: Robert Owens, with 14 points, and Skip Mills, with 11. Michael Bennett came off the bench to finish with eight points, six rebounds and two assists. IUPUI's Brandon Cole scored 17 points and grabbed eight rebounds, and teammate Dannorris Harvey had 15 points and made nine of 11 free throws. Bradley had three assists, one block and two steals to add to his scoring and rebounding. Ball State outscored IUPUI 30-22 in the paint, but the Cardinals were held to 2-of-15 shooting from 3-point range. IUPUI finished 5-for-17 from behind the arc.
